=Description=

" the technological focus in the Semantic web as been largely on content that consists of text. However, the World Wide Web now contains huge volumes Multi-media content. Video, music, voice, etc. Plus, data is generated from human behavior, such as sites read, book purchases, content produced, etc. that can also help Intelligent_agents understand human meaning in digital content. The Semantic web, so far as I know, does not really address these types of behaviors.

Semiotics does address multi-dimensional human behaviors, and the different types of Multi-media content online. Anything that a human culture can understand, can be analyzed through Semiotics.

Text may still be represented with triadic annotation "tags" in the Semiotic web. For other types of content (music, movies, images, Three dimensional content), we should think about the Semiotic nature of that content. The question we should as is How does Semiosis happen with this form media? Then, we should think about a way to help computers understand the Representamen, Interpretant, and Object qualities of the sign in question."


